</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ukeltekakatheolis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Keltek aka Theolis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 94<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/30/02 1:46:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3200.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> What Worked Best For Me..</span><hr size=1> Last time I went to PoF was with PO..  <br>
In the past (distant past) I went pretty often with other guilds on other servers and tried the run to west wall thingy.  The cons to this are the fact that there is always a noob or 4 who get lost and go east instead of west if you don't go as a group.  Also, the wanderers tend to run around before following you to the wall and they can if you aren't lucky bring half the zone with them.<br>
<br>
The first time with PO was with characters level 50 to 56ish with fair to good equipment.  First we sent in an FD'er to scout. When just a few mobs were near the porter, we zoned in 2-3 well balanced groups to take down as many mobs in front of the porter as possible before safely evac'ing out to feerott.  If necessary we did this up to 2 times to clear most of the wandering mobs near the portal and a few surrounding it.  The pro's to this are, you can do this while waiting for stragglers to arrive, and after the entrance is clear you'll be surprised how easy it is to just walk over to the west wall as a group and not worry about any surprise aggro from across the zone.  It's also easy to spot and CR corpses that die right at the port in hill in case anything goes wrong.<br>
<br>
